5:
They visited you again, huh? What's
that, the fifth time this week?
9:
Ever since they failed with their
forceful tactics, they've taken to
asking me daily.
10:
They're not complete fools with bad
intentions, which is why I'm not
entirely sure how to deal with them.
14:
...If they were just a bunch of thugs, I
could've given them a good beating
and sent them on their way.
17:
Another failure! This is taking far too
much time and effort...
19:
Uh... Sir, don't you think we're being a
little too pushy about this?
21: I'm doing my best here, okay?!
23:
Is this lady even worth it? I get that
she's something else, but is she
THAT amazing?
25:
Hold your tongue. Words of dissent
are one thing, but this is another.
27:
I will not tolerate any slander
against the one who is blessed by
the Stars and their light. She is,
without a doubt, meant to be our
leader.
29:
...Apologies, sir. Was just blowing off
some steam and went too far.
32:
She truly belongs somewhere far
better than the treacherous halls of
the Kaleidoscope.
34:
I agree. She's made a fine mess of
my Kaleidoscope...
39:
It's been highly amusing watching
you assign such significance to her
meager powers.
41:
But even fools like you can be of use
to me.
47:
Firamelia, thank goodness you're
here! We could really use your help!
49:
Got a report about those folks from
the Church of Farlana entering the
Kaleidoscope, but they've been
there for hours and still haven't
come out!
51:
We sent search parties in, of course,
but there's been no hide or hair of
them! I bet you a distortion
swallowed 'em up!
55:
How many search parties did you
send in?
58: Uh, should be 6 of them... Why?
61:
Stars above, flames in hand, heed
my will and bestow upon us your
guidance.
66:
This should go smoothly with your
powers at our side!
68:
Take some time to prepare
yourselves while I scout ahead.
We're headed pretty deep!
76:
Slipped past all those defenses, did
you? You really do know how to get
on my nerves.
79:
Took the words right out of my
mouth. You've really outdone
yourself this time.
82:
This is as far as your efforts go. Step
away from those folks if you know
what's good for you.
90:
Do you truly believe I wasn't
prepared to receive you?
94:
Darkness dwelling within all
creation, reveal the secrets of this
mighty labyrinth!
98:
Again with this magic? You do
remember it doesn't work on me,
don't you?
102:
But of course, as much as it irritates
me.
105:
Yes, your unbending will in the face
of darkness serves you well, boorish
though it may be.
109:
Which is exactly why you wouldn't
understand how effective it is on
ordinary mortals.
114:
So this was your aim from the
beginning!
119:
Get up, worm. Be a good slave! Let
out all your doubts, your discontent...
Every bit of malice within!
127:
Tch, so uncivilized... How unlike you,
flame bearer!
130:
To leave even your rear unguarded!
Slaves, attack!
135:
I guide the lost, and watch over
those who stay their course.
136:
Even though our roads were never
aligned, I never once bore you ill will
you for it.
141:
What are you doing? Move! Cut this
woman down!
145:
I mean this to you as well, priest.
Now rise.
146:
I know you still have the strength to
walk! Or has a little bit of darkness
shaken your conviction?
157:
O sacred light... O Stars above, who
light my way!
164:
I am terribly sorry, Lady Firamelia... I
have failed you!
166:
You have not. But now isn't the time
for this!
170:
Oh, don't worry about me. I've grown
bored of this charade. You will face
your demise one day soon, and I will
be there to savor it!
175:
Mark my words, flame bearer! Step
no further into my domain!
179:
...What a sad man. I would have
helped him if he had only asked.
183:
You said you watch over those who
stay their course. Will you not
consider joining with us then?
185:
I am sorry, but I decide my own path
forward... and I know you wouldn't
allow for it.
188:
Besides, I have certain companions
I'd like to keep watching over for the
time being.
192:
Firamelia, are you okay?! We heard
tons of fighting and made our way
down as fast as we could!
194:
I'm just peachy! I appreciate the
concern though.
197:
It's all clear to me now. Stars are
meant to shine, freely and for all.
200:
It's about time we headed home,
don't you think? I'll lead the way.
